	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=58629><span id=Sage>Arasimus, Eater of Souls</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>573 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is posted originally by Tradesman under the Vah Shir Anvil info but it is pertinant here as well.<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>This is the quest for the 'Humming Luclinite Mallet' and 'Vah Shir Anvil' used in Shadowscream armor.<br><br>1. Go to Shar Vahl<br>2. Find and Hail Master Barkhem @ 190, neg 175<br>3. Say &quot;I am looking for work&quot;<br>4. Ask &quot;What Bloodlings?&quot;<br>5. Buy 1 or 2 Carapace Shield Frames (this is an 8 slot container costing 2gp, 9sp, 7cp<br>6. Gather 16 'A Bloodling Carapace' and combine 8 in each shield frame to make 2 Bloodling Shields. These are found in Shadeweaver's Thicket and are uncommon from a Cht`Thk Bloodlings (think these are level 3 or so) and the bloodlings unspawn from time to time to spawn worms which are a place holder.&nbsp;&nbsp;At 59 with my pet killing them in 1 hit and with sow on my pet to move faster it took about 2 hours to get 16 of them.<br>7. Go back to Master Barkhem and give him one shield at a time the shield and he will return you some exps and A Bloodling Carapace Plate.<br>8. Buy a Mail Sectional Mold from Apprentice Garr @ 225, neg 160 for 1pp, 7gp, 7sp, 6cp.<br>9. Buy 1 Nepeta Oil Extract from Chialle @ neg 500, pos 115 for 1gp, 6sp, 2cp. (Now I have seen her walking around, I think the vendor next to her has some also.<br>10. Go to the forage (inside the smith shop around the corner) and combine the following 4 items.<br>10a) A Bloodling Carapace Plate<br>10b) A Bloodling Carapace Plate<br>10c) A Mail Sectional Mold<br>10d) Nepeta Oil Extract<br>(I have 188 skill and this is trivial)<br>The result of the combine is: Bloodling Plate Mail.<br>11. Give Master Barkhem the Bloodling Plate Mail and he will give it back to you with a 'Vah Shir Apprentice Mallet' - Now if you can get the Mail from someone then you can save all the steps before 11.<br>12. Ask Master Barkhem &quot;What report order?&quot; (you will receive 'a shield repair order')<br>13. Bring that report to Khala Dun Jasir @ 1140, neg 275 (you will receive his dented shield).<br>14. Take his dented shield to a forge and combine that and the apprentice mallet which repairs it. (You will receive the mallet back and his Immaculate shield).<br>15. Talk with Master Barkhem and ask &quot;What report order?&quot; again to receive another 'a shield repair order'.<br>16. Return the repaired back to that guard and receive a work order.<br>17. Bring the report to Khala Dun Aihjin @ 1140, neg 150 (you will receive his dented shield).<br>18. Repeat steps 14, 15, and 16.<br>19. Bring the report to Khala Dun Bokh @ neg 1120, 135 (you will receive his dented shield).<br>20. Repeat steps 14, 15, and 16.<br>21. Bring the report to Khala Dun Koby @ neg 1120, 55 (you will receive his dented shield).<br>22. Repeat steps 14 and 16 (not 15 this time, last one).<br>23. Return to Master Barkhem and give him all 4 work orders that you got from the guards (Receive exps, faction for Guardians of Shar Vahl and 'Vah Shir Anvil' - the Anvil is Giant so make sure you have a spot to put it).<br>24. Ask Master Barkhem &quot;What is a spirit anchor?&quot;.<br>25. Ask Master Barkhem &quot;How is he binding the spirits?&quot;.<br>26. Ask Master Barkhem &quot;How do you rend shadows?&quot;.<br>27. Ask Master Barkhem &quot;How do you make shadow disks?&quot;. (You will receive an 8 slot container and will learn you need 1 swirling shadows and 1 metal bits (2 small piece of ore and 1 water flask) to make 1 shadow disk.<br>28. Collect the parts to make the 8 shadow disks and combine all 8 in the container.<br>29. Return the container and the apprentice mallet to Master Barkhem and receive faction with Guardians of Shar Vahl, exps and the 'Luclinite Mallet'.<br>30. Ask Master Barkhem 'How do I make humming orbs?' (1 shrieking substance, 1 wailing substance, 1 metal rings, 1 Luclinite Mallet and 1 Var Shir Anvil)<br>31. Make 3 Humming Orbs, Give Master Barkhem them and the Luclinite Mallet and you will be rewarded with more exps, faction and a Humming Luclinite Mallet.<br>Happy Smithing.<hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/profile.html?261411 target=akztarg>Arasimus (Kiggulak's Master)</a><br>Enchanter of 59 seasons on Firona Vie<br><br><br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/profile.html?138893 target=akztarg>Kiggulak MohthK'Tan (Arasimus' Pet)</a><br>Firiona Vie Greenblood of the 53rd Circle<br></td></tr>
